Environment setup, data ingestion, and data cleaning¶

Instructions¶

  • Use this notebook to unpack the LMP and capacity price data.
  • Make sure to update the revmpath, datapath, apikeys, and nsrdbparams variables in settings.py.
  • Note that ERCOT and ISONE nodes are not publicly accessible and must be requested from ISO representatives.

### IMPORTANT: Change to False for actual operation
test = True
###########

### Copy LMP data and write nodecounts and averages
markets = ['da','rt']
isos = ['CAISO','ERCOT','PJM','NYISO','ISONE']
for market in markets:
    for year in range(2010,2018):
        print(year, market)
        for iso in isos:
            try:
                pvvm.data.copylmps(iso, market, year, test=True)
            except FileNotFoundError:
                print('no data for {} {} {}'.format(iso,market,year))

Extract LMP node locations¶

In [6]:
dfnodes = {}
  • CAISO node locations are extracted from this map:
    • graphical version: http://www.caiso.com/PriceMap/Pages/default.aspx
    • xml version: http://wwwmobile.caiso.com/Web.Service.Chart/api/v1/ChartService/GetPriceContourMap
  • As noted in the function text, first download the xml file and save it at revmpath + 'CAISO/in/GetPriceContourMap.xml.

  • As described in http://ceepr.mit.edu/publications/working-papers/705, PJM node locations are taken as the centroid of the centers of all zip codes that list that node as the closest node, using this table from PJM: https://www.pjm.com/-/media/markets-ops/energy/lmp-model-info/zip-code-mapping.ashx (parent page at https://www.pjm.com/markets-and-operations/energy/lmp-model-info.aspx)

  • ERCOT node locations are extracted from a Monthly CRR Network Model file. Accessing this file requires registering as an "Independent Market Research Entity" at http://www.ercot.com/services/rq/imre and paying the associated fees. Once registered as an IMRE, go to https://mis.ercot.com/pps/tibco/mis/Pages/Grid+Information/Long+Term+Planning, then select 'CRR Network Model (Monthly)'. Download and unzip one of the available files and use the filepath as the input value for filepath_input. Example: revmpath+'ERCOT/in/rpt.00011205.0000000000000000.20170530.140432154.JUL2017MonthlyCRRNetworkModel/ 2017.JUL.Monthly.Auction.OneLineDiagram.kml'

Download and work up MISO LMP files as example¶

Download¶

In [4]:
iso = 'MISO'

#############
### Day-ahead
market = 'da'

###### Pre-201503
### Download zipped files
dates = pd.date_range('2010-01-01','2015-02-01',freq='MS')
dates = [date.strftime('%Y%m') for date in dates]
urls = [
    'https://docs.misoenergy.org/marketreports/{}_da_lmp_csv.zip'.format(date)
    for date in dates]
pvvm.data.download_file_series(
    urlstart='', urlend='', fileseries=urls, 
    filepath=revmpath+'{}/in/lmp/{}/zip/'.format(iso, market),
    sleeptime=60, 
)

### Unzip the monthly-packaged files
dates = pd.date_range('2010-01-01','2015-02-01',freq='MS')
dates = [date.strftime('%Y%m') for date in dates]
filepath = revmpath+'{}/in/lmp/{}/'.format(iso, market)
zipfiles = [filepath+'zip/'+date+'_da_lmp_csv.zip' for date in dates]

for file in zipfiles:
    zip_file = zipfile.ZipFile(file, 'r')
    zip_file.extractall(filepath)
    zip_file.close()

Package LMPs into complete dataframes¶

In [9]:
def lmppackage(iso, year, market='da', inpath=None):
    """
    """
    ### Set and make filepaths
    if (inpath is None) and (market == 'da'):
        inpath = revmpath + iso + '/io/lmp-nodal/{}/'.format(market)
    elif (inpath is None) and (market == 'rt'):
        inpath = {
            'CAISO': revmpath + 'CAISO/io/lmp-nodal/rt/rtm-yearly/',
            'ERCOT': revmpath + 'ERCOT/io/lmp-nodal/rt-year/',
            'MISO':  revmpath + 'MISO/io/lmp-nodal/rt/',
            'PJM':   revmpath + 'PJM/io/lmp-nodal/rt/',
            'NYISO': revmpath + 'NYISO/io/lmp-nodal/rt/',
            'ISONE': revmpath + 'ISONE/io/lmp-nodal/rt/',
        }
        inpath = inpath[iso]

    ### Get the input files
    infiles = glob(inpath+'*{}.gz'.format(year))
    assert len(infiles) > 0, 'no input LMP files found'

    ### Load and concat the input files
    dfs = {}
    for i, file in enumerate(tqdm_notebook(infiles, desc='{} {}'.format(market, year))):
        node = os.path.basename(file)
        node = node[:node.find('-')]
        df = pd.read_csv(file, index_col=0, names=['lmp'], squeeze=True)
        dfs[node] = df

    dflmp = pd.concat(dfs, axis=1, copy=False)
    
    return dflmp

outpath = datapath+'lmp/'
os.makedirs(outpath, exist_ok=True)

for market in ['da','rt']:
    for year in range(2010,2018):
        dflmp = lmppackage(iso=iso, year=year, market=market)
        dflmp.to_csv(
            '{}{}-lmp-{}-{}.gz'.format(
                outpath,iso.lower(), market, year),
            compression='gzip')

caisonodes = caisonodes.loc[caisonodes.area=='CA','node'].values
for market in markets:
    for year in tqdm_notebook(years, desc=market):
        df = pvvm.io.getdflmp('CAISO',market,year).loc[:,caisonodes].dropna(axis=1)

        ### Write the average files

        percentiles = [0.005, 0.01, 0.025, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 
                       0.75, 0.9, 0.975, 0.99, 0.995]
        df.T.describe(percentiles=percentiles).T.to_csv(
            meanoutpath+'lmp-{}-{}-CAonly-percentiles.csv'.format(market, year))

        elif (iso == 'ERCOT') or ((iso == 'ISONE') and (market == 'rt')):

# inpath = revmpath+'Package/pvvm/data/lmp/'
inpath = datapath+'lmp/'
years = list(range(2010,2018))
isos = ['CAISO','ERCOT','MISO','PJM','NYISO','ISONE']
resolutions = {
    'da': dict(zip(isos, 6*[60])),
    'rt': {'CAISO':5,'ERCOT':5,'MISO':60,'PJM':60,'NYISO':5,'ISONE':60}
}
percentiles = [0.025, 0.25, 0.75, 0.975]

###### Only nodes with geographic information
dictgeo = {}
for market in ['da','rt']:
    # for iso in ['NYISO','PJM']:
    for iso in isos:
        resolution = resolutions[market][iso]
        
        ### Get the geo nodes
        dfnodes = pvvm.io.get_iso_nodes(iso)
        if iso == 'CAISO':
            nodes = dfnodes.loc[dfnodes.area=='CA','node'].astype(str).tolist()
        else:
            nodes = dfnodes['node'].astype(str).tolist()
        
        for year in tqdm_notebook(years, desc='{} {}'.format(market,iso)):
            infile = inpath+'{}-lmp-{}-{}.gz'.format(iso.lower(), market, year)
            try:
                df = pd.read_csv(
                    infile, index_col=0, parse_dates=True,
                ).tz_convert(pvvm.toolbox.tz_iso[iso])
                ### Get the shared nodes
                datanodes = [node for node in df.columns.astype(str).tolist() if node in nodes]
                ### Calculate number of negative intervals for each node,
                ### and describe trends across all nodes
                dictgeo[market, iso, year] = (
                    (df[datanodes] < 0).astype(int).sum(axis=0) 
                    / pvvm.toolbox.yearhours(year) / (60 / resolution)
                )
            except FileNotFoundError:
                print(infile)

dffull = pd.concat(dictgeo).reset_index().rename(
    columns={'level_0':'market','level_1':'ISOwecc','level_2':'year','level_3':'node',0:'negative'}
)

for market in ['da','rt']:
    # for iso in ['NYISO','PJM']:
    for iso in isos:
        resolution = resolutions[market][iso]
        
        ### Get the geo nodes
        dfnodes = pvvm.io.get_iso_nodes(iso)
        if iso == 'CAISO':
            nodes = dfnodes.loc[dfnodes.area=='CA','node'].astype(str).tolist()
        else:
            nodes = dfnodes['node'].astype(str).tolist()
        
        for year in tqdm_notebook(years, desc='{} {}'.format(market,iso)):
            infile = inpath+'{}-lmp-{}-{}.gz'.format(iso.lower(), market, year)
            try:
                df = pd.read_csv(
                    infile, index_col=0, parse_dates=True,
                ).tz_convert(pvvm.toolbox.tz_iso[iso])
                ### Get the shared nodes
                datanodes = [node for node in df.columns.astype(str).tolist() if node in nodes]
                ### Calculate number of negative intervals for each node,
                ### and describe trends across all nodes
                dicthourly[market, iso, year] = (
                    (df[datanodes] < 0).astype(int).groupby(df.index.hour).sum() 
                    / pvvm.toolbox.yearhours(year) / (60 / resolution) * 24
                ).T.describe(percentiles=percentiles)
            except FileNotFoundError:
                print(infile)
                
dfhourly = pd.concat(dicthourly)
dfhourly[24] = dfhourly[0].copy()

dfplot = pd.DataFrame(dfhourly).reset_index().rename(
    columns={'level_0':'market','level_1':'ISO','level_2':'year','level_3':'stat',}
)

dfplot['datum'] = dfplot.market + '_' + dfplot.ISO + '_' + dfplot.year.astype(str)
